Ruled by simple particle physics algorithms, this simulation allows to contemplate the similarities between stellar and neural dynamics, galactic and brain matters.

Each one of the 60 frames per second is a unique generative composition.

metadata.name: Akuma ðŸ‘¹ #41
metadata.description:
ðŸ‘¹Akuma means Demon in Japanese. This series takes inspiration in manga and samourai movies, and are the direct descendents of my Codevember Walker and Titan series, featuring creative coding to give life and personality to "Walkers".

Each Akuma is part of an imaginary world and walks endlessly in their own way: elegant for fews, terrifying for others, peaceful for somes.. 

To re-enforced their personality and play with the concept of fx-hash I teamed-up with the musician & composer Faubourg to add a generative sound track, now each Akuma has his own track from around ~3200 possibilities and the solo-lead(10%) and solo-pad (1%) have their own visual universe, but I will not spoil you more ;)

ðŸŽ¶Note : You need to click to play the music and make your akuma heart beating .

Click once : Start the music and make your akuma heart beating 
Drag : Control the camera 
Pinch / mouse-wheel : Zoom
Enjoy!

Tw makio64
Faubourg : https://linktr.ee/faubourg

PS:The profit of this NFT will be shared with Faubourg

metadata.name: Bifurcation Rains #93
metadata.description:
When you look at the cityscape outside the window through the glass with the raindrops, it always seems to be undecided about its choice of state and position in space. It flows and wriggles, becoming fluid, half-river, half-thought-out fantasy. 
Bifurcation diagrams are visually similar to these traces left by water on glass. We have tried to imagine a moving world, which right now is at a point of choice.

Made with love, AI and p5.js code
To save the image, press the 's' key. Enjoy!

October, 2022
Julia V & YulikolaY

metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #3491
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
Made with love by culla using p5.js

metadata.name: Bleached #74
metadata.description:
Bleached is a work inspired by mid-20th century art. I have always been impressed by its beauty and charm of non-ideality. How art gave birth to order out of utter chaos.
Inspired, I transferred the spirit of its freedom and expression into my algorithm.

metadata.name: Rite of Passage #266
metadata.description:
In life, we all take different paths, different rites of passage, and while the end is all that's ever true, we will still all view it and experience it in very different ways, like that masterpiece hanging on the wall at the end of our gallery visit. 
  

There are always things that we will never have the power to change, but at the same time, we determine the route, we influence the journey, we can choose the person we want to be. We'll look back on memories, we'll have regrets, and we'll think about what could have been - but unlike this artwork, in the end we won't be able to change the final output by simply pressing a number - so live well and be happy my friends. 

---------------------

Generative artwork by Sykcolo / @sykcoloart

Primary sale proceeds:
50% to Processing Foundation
50% to Savepakistan

Royalties:
50% to the original minter
50% to artist (me)

Press '2' to '4' to see what could have been + increase pixel density. 
Press 's' to save

Details:

150 hand-picked colour pallets (thanks to @SteveMakerspace for colour selection method)
2 Frame types
4 Art types
2 Times of day (light or dark background)

License: MIT

Happy Birthday fxhash

metadata.name: Celestial Rings: Algorithmic Study #23
metadata.description:
This is an exploration to create an abstract artwork using fields and growth rings and their interaction with each other. Each of the mints can have several central rings up to 14 and the rings interact with each other to form a larger structure. The structure of the rings can be uniform or rotating, with mixed colors or mono colors. Various color palettes and canvas sizes have been used.

Open it in live view and press â€™sâ€™ to save image with high resolution.

Made with p5js.
